---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Abhishek Mohanty — Oracle HCM Cloud Technical Lead, Oracle ACE Apprentice, AIOUG member.">
  <article class="prose-container about">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Abhishek Mohanty</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Oracle HCM Cloud Technical Lead writing notes from the field — mostly on
      Fast Formulas, but also anything else that bites me in production.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm an <strong>Oracle ACE Apprentice</strong> and a member of the
      <strong>All India Oracle Users Group (AIOUG)</strong>. Over the last decade I've
      worked across most of the modules in Oracle HCM Cloud — Core HR, Absence Management,
      Time and Labor, Compensation, Benefits, Payroll, Recruiting, Redwood, HDL, and OTBI —
      with a heavy lean toward the techno-functional side. Most of my recent delivery has
      been multi-country APAC implementations: Taiwan, Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines,
      Hong Kong, Thailand.
    </p>

    <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
    <p>
      Oracle's documentation is excellent at telling you <em>what</em> a feature does, and
      mostly silent on the <em>edges</em> — the way <code>IV_ACCRUAL</code> actually
      behaves inside a matrix accrual, why <code>ESS_LOG_WRITE</code> blows up in 26A
      when used inside a Global Absence Carryover formula, what happens to
      <code>PER_ASG_REL_ORIGINAL_DATE_OF_HIRE</code> after a Global Transfer. These are
      the things I write down here, partly so I can find them again, and partly because
      somebody else is going to hit the same wall.
    </p>

    <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Production-ready Fast Formulas with named-employee worked examples</li>
      <li>Debug logging idioms for every formula type that has them</li>
      <li>Multi-country APAC patterns — leave policies, accrual matrices, TER/TCR</li>
      <li>Redwood and HDL Transformation Formula notes</li>
      <li>Occasional rants about things that broke in a release upgrade</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Standing on the shoulders of</h2>
    <p>
      Big thanks to the AIOUG community, the global Oracle ACE program, and the
      colleagues and functional leads I've learned the craft from over the years.
      Mistakes and bad takes here are entirely my own.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <p class="muted small">
      The notes on this site are personal and reflect the author's views, not those of
      any employer or client. Oracle and the Oracle product names referenced are
      trademarks of Oracle Corporation.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 1em 0 2em;
  }
  .small { font-size: 0.85rem; }
</style>
